<!-- Attire -->
<div id="attire" class="panel services">
    <div class="content">
          <div class="row">
      <div class="col-xs-6">
              <div class="media" align="center">
                <div class="pull-left">
          <div class="circular-tux"></div>
          <div class="circular-mshoes"></div>
          <div class="circular-bowtie"></div>
          <div class="circular-mextras"></div>
                </div>
        <div class="media-body" style="border-right: 2px solid #999;">
          <h3 class="media-heading">Men's Attire</h3>
            Men are expected to wear a tuxedo, preferably a white tie tuxedo. The bridal party will be getting their tuxedo's from <a href="http://www.princetontuxedo.com/">Princeton Tuxedo</a> and have a group discount. If you are interested in joining the group please let someone from the wedding party know. Top hats and bowties are also not required wear but preferred! Any questions about mens attire, or if you aren't sure what to wear, please reach out to the bride or her maid of honor and ask. 
        </div>
      </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-xs-6">
        <div class="media" align="center">
                <div class="pull-right">
          <div class="circular-gown"></div>
          <div class="circular-makeup"></div>
          <div class="circular-jewelry"></div>
          <div class="circular-accessories"></div>
                </div>
        <div class="media-body">
          <h3 class="media-heading">Women's Attire</h3>
          For women the expected attire is a ball or evening gown in the white or black tie style. Black tie style being a non-bright color and a floor length evening gown. White tie style being a neutral color and a ball gown. Women are also encouraged to wear makeup and dramatic jewelry to enhance the white tie affair atmosphere. As always, any questions about womens attire can be directed to the bride or maid of honor. If you're not sure, ask! 
        </div>
      </div>
      </div>
    </div>
